          <actionDate>2015-06-16</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p align="left"><strong>Capital Access for Small Business Banks Act </strong></p> <p align="left">This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a bank or a depository institution holding company which is an S corporation to: (1) have 500 shareholders (the current limit is 100 shareholders), and (2) issue qualified preferred bank stock. The bill makes a distribution of qualified preferred bank stock to a shareholder includible in the gross income of the shareholder and allows the bank or holding company to deduct the amount of such distribution. </p> <p align="left" /> <p align="left" />]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
